com.android.database.tables

Class Controllers

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.android.database.tables.Controllers
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    DBHelper.TableIF

    public class Controllers
extends Object
implements DBHelper.TableIF
    Class that is representing table with the same name in application's database. This is a helper class that generates queries relevant to the table that this class represents. The example below shows how to deal with any Map type arguments such as "newValues" in DBHelper.sql_insert_row(Class, Map, boolean): Map<String,String> newValues = new HashMap<String,String>(); newValues.put(Controllers.DBSchema.COLUMN_1, "Name"); newValues.put(Controllers.DBSchema.COLUMN_2, DBHelper.CONTROLLER_TYPE_MOUSE); Controllers.SQL_UPDATE_ROW(1, newValues); where the keys are the names of the columns in the corresponding table, which this class represents.
